        public static boolean isOlder(java.lang.String time1,
                              java.lang.String time2)
        Determine if the first time-formatted string is older than the second time-formatted string. Note that order is important!

        isOlder(time1, time2) != isOlder(time2, time1),
        for given time-formatted Strings time1, time2.

        The strings follow the following format:
        YYYY-MM-DD-hh-mm-ss
        e.g. 2020-03-25-18-35-22
        Parameters:
        time1 - first time-formatted String
        time2 - second time-formatted String
        Returns:
        whether

      • timeSince

        public static int timeSince(java.lang.String time1,
                            java.lang.String time2)
        Calculates the difference in time (in seconds) between the provided time-formatted Strings.

        The string format is as follows:
        YYYY-MM-DD-hh-mm-ss

        The difference is calculated by the formula:
        newer_time - older_time

        This means that the order of the parameters DOES NOT MATTER
        Parameters:
        time1 - first time-formatted String
        time2 - second time-formatted String
        Returns:
        (int) the number of seconds between the two times

      • largestCoprime

        public static int largestCoprime(int num,
                                 int numDigits)
        Finds the largest n-digit coprime to the provided integer, where numDigits is the number of digits in the coprime number
        Parameters:
        num - (int) number to determine coprimes
        numDigits - (int) number of digits the coprime must have.
        Returns:
        (int) largest coprime with n-digits to num, -1 if such a coprime does not exist, -2 for any errors.
